<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  macOS Info.plist additions for Warehouse14 POS.

  Tauri 2's bundler MERGES this file into the generated app bundle's
  Info.plist (it does not replace the auto-generated one). We only declare
  the privacy usage strings the WKWebview needs.

  Why this is required for the in-app camera (Foto-Werkstatt):
    The WKWebview only exposes `navigator.mediaDevices` / `getUserMedia`
    once the host app declares a camera usage description. Without
    NSCameraUsageDescription the packaged macOS build leaves
    `navigator.mediaDevices` UNDEFINED (the exact "MediaDevices API nicht
    verfügbar" symptom) and, if it were reached, TCC would hard-kill the
    process. wry >= 0.37 auto-grants the WKWebview media-capture request,
    so once this string is present the OS shows the standard one-time
    camera-permission prompt on first use and the live viewfinder works.

  The strings are shown verbatim by macOS in the permission dialog, so
  they are written in professional German (Sie-Form) for the operator.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Warehouse14 benötigt Zugriff auf die Kamera, um in der Foto-Werkstatt Produkt- und Ausweisfotos aufzunehmen.</string>
  </dict>
</plist>
